&gt;&gt; Could you comment briefly
about the success of Vietnamese

00:27:03.260 --> 00:27:03.326
in the United States and also--

00:27:05.260 --> 00:27:06.793
&gt;&gt; The success of what?

00:27:07.260 --> 00:27:08.260
I didn't--

00:27:09.260 --> 00:27:10.260
&gt;&gt; Vietnamese.

00:27:11.260 --> 00:27:12.260
&gt;&gt; Vietnamese.

00:27:13.260 --> 00:27:15.526
And also just a comment that the
congressional seat formerly held

00:27:15.260 --> 00:27:17.060
by Cokie's parents is now held
by a Vietnamese republican.

00:27:17.260 --> 00:27:18.260
&gt;&gt; That's true.

00:27:19.260 --> 00:27:20.993
The Vietnamese are a great
success story in this country.

00:27:21.260 --> 00:27:21.393
Few people are more hard working

00:27:23.260 --> 00:27:23.926
and few people struggle
more to get here.

00:27:25.260 --> 00:27:27.060
The fam-- the Vietnamese family
in my book tried to escape

00:27:27.260 --> 00:27:28.063
from Vietnam sit-- you know, a
dozen times and he finally escaped.

00:27:30.790 --> 00:27:33.390
They were floating
free on the open sea.

00:27:34.370 --> 00:27:35.433
The engine had conked out in their
boat and the mother [inaudible]

00:27:37.640 --> 00:27:40.906
and the family said to me
to save my two children.

00:27:42.690 --> 00:27:46.490
The next thing I was going to
do was have to slit my wrist

00:27:46.490 --> 00:27:48.490
and feed my children my blood.

00:27:49.450 --> 00:27:50.193
Now, it didn't come to that
because they saw land the next day.

00:27:52.840 --> 00:27:53.626
But in that period, in Southeast
Asia, if you washed up on the shore

00:27:56.520 --> 00:27:58.453
of Cambodia, you'd be killed.

00:27:58.520 --> 00:27:58.813
And if you washed up on the
shore of Thailand you'd be safe.

00:28:02.160 --> 00:28:02.163
And you could imagine the moment
when my student's father stood

00:28:06.290 --> 00:28:06.876
in the [inaudible] with that
boat and called out where are we?

00:28:09.770 --> 00:28:12.570
Literally it was a life
and death question.

00:28:13.520 --> 00:28:15.386
Fortunately, it was Thailand

00:28:15.700 --> 00:28:16.590
and then eventually the
family found sanctuary

00:28:17.810 --> 00:28:18.616
in the Philippines before
they came to America.

00:28:20.070 --> 00:28:20.520
And that child, my student
was born in the refugee camp

00:28:23.220 --> 00:28:26.420
in the Philippines and
her name today is Thai Phi

00:28:26.700 --> 00:28:28.766
for the two countries, Thailand

00:28:29.660 --> 00:28:32.526
and the Philippines
that gave her sanctuary.

00:28:32.560 --> 00:28:36.226
Her family is not unusual,
the struggle and the tenacity

00:28:37.140 --> 00:28:41.140
and the courage that her family
showed to escape from Vietnam

00:28:43.000 --> 00:28:46.266
and survive that hardship
is just one tiny chapter

00:28:47.200 --> 00:28:47.310
of this marvelous story that
immigrants are writing everyday.

